# MES module context (caveman)

- Path: Modules/MES only.
- Root rules = base law. Always follow.
- This file = extra MES law.

- MES need ERP. No ERP, MES no run.
- Use Core shared parts. Do not clone logic.
- Keep MES boundaries clean. No random cross-module edits.

- ProductionOrder number: use ERP DocumentType + DocumentNumberAllocator pattern.
- ProductionOrder link to SalesOrder: keep header `sales_order_id` and line `sales_order_line_id` consistent.
- Stock movement: MES define contract, ERP adapter execute with ERP stock service.
- Tracing on items: none|lot|serial. Migration reversible.
- Heavy KPI/OEE/capacity calc: materialize with jobs + cache, not live recompute.
- Emit typed MES domain events (production, operation, quality, downtime, lot/serial).
- High-value MES models use DIFF versioning/audit strategy.

- Core change impact big. ERP change impact medium. Be careful.
- If requirement unclear or risky: stop and ask user.
